org.chronos.chronodb.internal.impl.query.parser.token

Class WhereToken.DoubleWhereDetails

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.chronos.chronodb.internal.impl.query.parser.token.WhereToken.AbstractWhereDetails<java.lang.Double,NumberCondition>
      • org.chronos.chronodb.internal.impl.query.parser.token.WhereToken.DoubleWhereDetails
  • Enclosing class:
    WhereToken

    public class WhereToken.DoubleWhereDetails
extends WhereToken.AbstractWhereDetails<java.lang.Double,NumberCondition>
    A simple data container, specifying the details of a WhereToken in the query language.

    This version is specialized for "where" clauses that act on Double values.

    • Method Detail

      • getEqualityTolerance

        public double getEqualityTolerance()
        Returns the assigned equality tolerance.

        The equality tolerance is the (absolute) value by which two double values can differ and still be considered equal.

        Returns:
        The equality tolerance. Never negative.

      • setEqualityTolerance

        The equality tolerance is the (absolute) value by which two double values can differ and still be considered equal.
